title: For Sale/Trade:  National Ordnance Inc. M1 Carbine
postcontent: I am selling my post war commercial made M1 Carbine manufactured by National Ordnance Inc.  The rifle is a close copy of the original GI M1 Carbine, and national ordnance Inc was one of the commercial manufactures to use some GI parts to make their rifles. While not as quality as a real carbine, these particular rifles have a much better reputation than some other commercial manufactures. This rifle has a beautiful clean wood stock, metal heat shield, and flip rear battle sight. The metal finish is poor, but there is very little surface rust and no pitting.  The gun functions well, but it was recommended by a gunsmith that a new spring be put in as the bolt has some trouble picking up rounds out of the magazine. These springs are easy to find and affordable. All in all this rifle would be great as a plinker, restoration project, or home defense carbine.  The ONLY trades I will consider is for military surplus rifles or pistols (1946 or earlier)  Plenty of pictures available on request.
